{{ 'dev-three-step.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
<script src="{{ 'dev-three-step.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>

{%- comment -%} Fixed design tokens from Figma — not merchant-controlled {%- endcomment -%}
<style>
  .dev-three-step {

    /* No --container-max: the card row is hug-width and centred, there is no
       centred max-width frame in the artboard. The inset is all --section-px.
       Mobile is deliberately full-bleed (0), so the photos run edge to edge. */
    --section-px: 64px;
    --section-px-mobile: 0px;
    --pt-mobile: 0px;

    /* Mobile has no cards: each step carries its own 48px top padding, which is
       what produces the 403px step pitch on the mobile artboard. */
    --step-pt-mobile: 48px;

    /* Mobile/Title 3 — same 24px on both artboards. */
    --font-heading-size: 24px;
    --font-heading-weight: 500;
    --font-heading-lh: 1.2;

    /* Body drops Lg (18) → Md (16) on mobile; the artboard states its own size,
       so it wins over a scale factor. */
    --font-body-size: 18px;
    --font-body-size-mobile: 16px;
    --font-body-weight: 500;
    --font-body-lh: 1.4;

    --card-radius: 32px;
    --card-pad: 32px;
    /* 332 media + 2x32 padding + 2x1 border. The card is hug-width in Figma; in CSS it must be
       stated, or the text block's `width: 100%` has nothing to resolve against. */
    --card-w: 398px;
    /* The active card is the same width but taller: 64px block padding vs 32px. */
    --card-pad-active-block: 64px;
    --text-w-active: 300px;

    --media-w: 332px;
    --media-h: 250px;
    --media-radius: 16px;

    --gap-cards: 24px;
    --gap-card-inner: 24px;
    --gap-text: 8px;
    --text-px: 16px;

    --controls-pt: 24px;
    --controls-gap: 16px;
    --arrow-pad: 19px;
    --arrow-radius: 60px;
    --icon-size: 24px;
    --dot-size: 8px;
    --dot-gap: 16px;

    --transition: 300ms;
  }
</style>

{%- comment -%}
  Every class is `dev-`-prefixed on purpose. Horizon compiles the {% stylesheet %} block of EVERY
  stock section into one sheet that loads on EVERY page, so an unprefixed BEM name silently inherits
  stock rules (this exact trap broke dev-announcement-bar). Do not drop the prefix.
{%- endcomment -%}
<div
  class="dev-three-step"
  style="
    --bg: {{ section.settings.background_color }};
    --color: {{ section.settings.text_color }};
    --card-bg: {{ section.settings.card_color }};
    --border-color: {{ section.settings.border_color }};
    --pt: {{ section.settings.padding_top }}px;
    --pb: {{ section.settings.padding_bottom }}px;
  "
>
  <div class="dev-three-step__inner">
    {%- comment -%}
      One scroll-snap track at every width. At >=1280 all three cards fit, so it never scrolls and
      the arrows/dots only move the highlight — exactly the desktop artboard. Between 769 and 1279
      the same track scrolls instead of squashing the cards to unreadable slivers (no Figma reference
      exists at those widths, so the rule there is: never overflow the page, never overlap).
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <ul class="dev-three-step__track" role="list">
      {%- for block in section.blocks -%}
        {%- liquid
          assign img = block.settings.image
          assign img_alt = block.settings.image_alt | strip_html | escape
        -%}
        <li
          class="dev-three-step__card{% if forloop.first %} dev-three-step__card--active{% endif %}"
          data-three-step-card
          {{ block.shopify_attributes }}
        >
          <div class="dev-three-step__text">
            {%- if block.settings.title != blank -%}
              {%- comment -%} inline_richtext: already safe HTML from Shopify — never escape it. {%- endcomment -%}
              {%- comment -%}
              A <p>, not a heading. These are the labels on a row of cards, and the section carries
              no heading of its own — so as an <h3> each one hung off whatever heading happened to
              precede it in the document, and on the homepage that produced a literal h1 -> h3 skip.
              They are captions, not sections. The class does all the styling, so nothing moves.
            {%- endcomment -%}
            <p class="dev-three-step__title">{{ block.settings.title }}</p>
            {%- endif -%}

            {%- if block.settings.body != blank -%}
              <div class="dev-three-step__body">{{ block.settings.body }}</div>
            {%- endif -%}
          </div>

          <div class="dev-three-step__media">
            {%- if img != blank -%}
              {%- comment -%}
                The media box is 332 x 250 on desktop and 100vw x 250 on mobile — fixed height,
                fluid width, object-fit: cover. The source was requested at its own aspect and the
                browser cropped it. Measured at a 500px viewport / DPR 2:

                  box      489 x 250 CSS  ->  978 x 500 device
                  shipped  1000 x 800     ->  37% of the height downloaded and discarded
                  image 1  212,968 B, against 24,278 B for image 3 in the identical box

                1.3 is one ratio for both breakpoints, and it is the desktop box (332 / 250 = 1.328)
                rounded DOWN rather than the mobile one: mobile only gets wider as the viewport
                grows (1.5 at 375, 3.07 at 768), so the desktop tile is the tallest box either
                breakpoint asks for and a crop no wider than it can never run out of height. The
                floor is a 320px phone at 1.28, where 1.3 is 1.5% short — below anything visible.

                CDN, 664x500 at q80: image 1  212,968 -> 85,188, image 2  62,278 -> 30,360,
                image 3  24,278 -> 13,508. The spread between the three is the sources, not the
                settings; image 1 is simply a busier photograph.

                These are .webp sources today, where `quality` is legal, but the setting is an
                image_picker and the next upload could be a png — which makes image_url raise
                "quality can't be used with ext png" and renders the src as an error string. Hence
                the extension check rather than a bare quality argument.
              {%- endcomment -%}
              {%- liquid
                comment
                  Base 1536 = the top of the ladder. `image_tag` drops every `widths:` entry wider
                  than the base url and says nothing about it, so a base of 1000 capped the srcset
                  three rungs early. The base itself is only the `src` fallback.
                endcomment
                assign step_ext = img | image_url: width: 1 | split: '?' | first | split: '.' | last | downcase
                if step_ext == 'gif'
                  assign step_src = img | image_url: width: 1536, height: 1182, crop: 'center'
                elsif step_ext == 'png'
                  assign step_src = img | image_url: width: 1536, height: 1182, crop: 'center', format: 'webp', quality: 70
                else
                  assign step_src = img | image_url: width: 1536, height: 1182, crop: 'center', quality: 70
                endif
              -%}
              {{
                step_src
                | image_tag:
                  loading: 'lazy',
                  widths: '332, 400, 500, 600, 664, 760, 860, 1000, 1150, 1300, 1536',
                  sizes: '(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 332px',
                  alt: img_alt,
                  class: 'dev-three-step__image'
              }}
            {%- endif -%}
          </div>
        </li>
      {%- endfor -%}
    </ul>

    {%- if section.blocks.size > 1 -%}
      <div class="dev-three-step__controls">
        <button
          type="button"
          class="dev-three-step__arrow dev-three-step__arrow--prev"
          aria-label="{{ 'accessibility.slideshow_previous' | t | escape }}"
        >
          {%- comment -%} Exported from Figma (Icon/Outline/arrow-narrow-left) — path data verbatim. {%- endcomment -%}
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
            <path d="M7 8L3 12L7 16M3 12L21 12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </button>

        <ul class="dev-three-step__dots" role="list">
          {%- for block in section.blocks -%}
            <li class="dev-three-step__dot-item">
              <button
                type="button"
                class="dev-three-step__dot"
                data-three-step-dot
                aria-current="{% if forloop.first %}true{% else %}false{% endif %}"
                aria-label="{{ block.settings.title | strip_html | default: forloop.index | escape }}"
              ></button>
            </li>
          {%- endfor -%}
        </ul>

        <button
          type="button"
          class="dev-three-step__arrow dev-three-step__arrow--next"
          aria-label="{{ 'accessibility.slideshow_next' | t | escape }}"
        >
          {%- comment -%} Exported from Figma (Icon/Outline/arrow-narrow-right) — path data verbatim. {%- endcomment -%}
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
            <path d="M17 16L21 12L17 8M21 12L3 12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </button>
      </div>
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>
</div>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Three step",
  "tag": "section",
  "settings": [
    { "type": "header", "content": "Colors" },
    { "type": "color", "id": "background_color", "label": "Background", "default": "#FFFCF4" },
    { "type": "color", "id": "text_color", "label": "Text color", "default": "#333333" },
    { "type": "color", "id": "card_color", "label": "Active card background", "default": "#FCF5E3", "info": "The cream fill on the highlighted step. Desktop only — mobile has no cards." },
    { "type": "color", "id": "border_color", "label": "Card border & inactive dot", "default": "#C4BCA9" },

    { "type": "header", "content": "Spacing" },
    { "type": "range", "id": "padding_top", "min": 0, "max": 120, "step": 4, "unit": "px", "label": "Padding top", "default": 80, "info": "Desktop only. On mobile each step carries its own 48px top padding, per the artboard." },
    { "type": "range", "id": "padding_bottom", "min": 0, "max": 120, "step": 4, "unit": "px", "label": "Padding bottom", "default": 0 }
  ],
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "step",
      "name": "Step",
      "limit": 6,
      "settings": [
        { "type": "inline_richtext", "id": "title", "label": "Title", "default": "Step 1" },
        { "type": "richtext", "id": "body", "label": "Text", "default": "<p>Our duvets started life as a tree. Think eucalyptus.</p>" },
        { "type": "image_picker", "id": "image", "label": "Image", "info": "Leave empty on the first three steps to use the photo bundled with the theme." },
        { "type": "text", "id": "image_alt", "label": "Image alt text" }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "Three step",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "step",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Step 1",
            "body": "<p>Our duvets started life as a tree. Think eucalyptus.</p>",
            "image_alt": "Stacked eucalyptus logs"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "step",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Step 2",
            "body": "<p>Using water, it’s transformed into ultra-fine fibres, smoother than merino wool.</p>",
            "image_alt": "Close-up of ultra-fine tree fibre"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "step",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Step 3",
            "body": "<p>Collected, filled then sewn together, it adapts to heat in sleep for all seasons. Year round.</p>",
            "image_alt": "A duvet being sewn on a machine"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
